From cdetermanjr at gmail.com  Wed Jul  1 20:37:28 2015
From: cdetermanjr at gmail.com (Charles Determan)
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2015 13:37:28 -0500
Subject: [R-sig-hpc] Installing gputools fails on Ubuntu 14.04LTS
In-Reply-To: <CACjNfm=REZbpTWTRuYbVFqZkNpqkodkFc65iZmSV8eL6SVhwLQ@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CACjNfm=REZbpTWTRuYbVFqZkNpqkodkFc65iZmSV8eL6SVhwLQ@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <CAKxd1KOff-YgEV0YYXuR+KY1kME1rwoqd1LR85ibsWYmKWKtQQ@mail.gmail.com>

If you download directory from the github repo you aren't provided with a
'configure' file but the 'configure.ac' file (which is in the src/
directory of your gputools directory).  As such none of compilation
instructions, which are rather complex for CUDA, are being passed to your
compiler which will create the gputools.so file you are looking for.  You
first need use the 'autoconf' program to create the 'configure' file.

autoconf configure.ac > configure
# make executable
chmod +x configure

Then try it again, report back if you have further problems.

Regards,

Charles

